commit.message:
Add status_path label to connected_clients server metric.

This fixes an issue where the exporter would fail to work if a user
attempted to monitor multiple OpenVPN processes in server mode as the
metrics would clash without the status_path label.
CHANGELOG.md added.

commit.message:
add openvpn_connected_clients 

+ dockerfile + minor go review
Explicitly close open files
Fix username/virtual address on client metrics
Deduplicate the metrics.
Update the README to list the actual metrics that are exported.
Add a script for building a statically linked version of the exporter.

Replace client and route counters by per-entry metrics.

This allows us to graph either per-connection or the total bandwidth
of the VPN server.

Fixes #2
*Really* use the right timezone when parsing timestamps.
Use the right timezone for the timestamps in the client stats.
Mention the TCP port number in the docs.
Add example output.
